# Tasks — `<feature-name>`

> Ordered checklist that implements `design.md` and proves
> `requirements.md`. Mark `[x]` only when the task is genuinely done —
> the reviewer refuses to close a feature with unticked boxes.
>
> Every implementation task that produces verifiable behaviour must have
> at least one corresponding test task. Every test task references the
> R-ids it covers, so the traceability is local and grep-friendly.

## Implementation

- [ ] T1 — `<implementation step>` *(Covers: R1)*
- [ ] T2 — `<implementation step>` *(Covers: R2)*
- [ ] T3 — `<implementation step>` *(Covers: R3, R4)*

## Tests

- [ ] T4 — `<test name>` — happy path for `<concern>` *(Covers: R1)*
- [ ] T5 — `<test name>` — error path for `<failure>` *(Covers: R4)*
- [ ] T6 — `<test name>` — `<edge case>` *(Covers: R2, R3)*

## Closure

- [ ] `./init.sh` exits `0`
- [ ] Every R-id in `requirements.md` is covered by at least one ticked test task above
- [ ] `progress/impl_<feature-name>.md` carries the implementer's notes
- [ ] `progress/review_<feature-name>.md` carries the reviewer's verdict (APPROVE)
- [ ] Feature transitioned to `done` via `korva harness done <id>`
